ver reason, it now qualifies as a collectible item. So plenty of people collect old chips, buy them at auctions, or sell them to other collectors. Indeed, it’s perfectly legal to sell, buy, and collect old chips as collectible items. And as you can guess from the title of this section, collecting chips is called exonumia. The price of these collectible items ranges from as low as $5 to as high as $500. The price of an antique casino token depends on the date of manufacture, the state it’s in, its relative rarity, or some special features; just as you would expect with other antiquities in general. And since we’ve just acquainted ourselves with antique chips, let’s meet one more special type of token — the nonmaterial ones!\r\n<h2>Virtual Gambling — Chips in Online Casinos</h2>\r\nIn brick-and-mortar casinos, chips stand for real money. In online casinos, real money stands for chips. Wait, what? Confused...? We’ll explain now!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-290\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/picspree-874707.jpg\" alt=\"Chips in Casino\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" />\r\n\r\nOnline casinos often use the term “free chips,” which stands for a real-money bonus. You can get free chips at an online casino; even for games that don’t feature chips per se, such as slots. However, online casinos, chips don’t always stand for bonuses and promotions; they often represent real chips at virtual table games. This way, when you play online poker or online blackjack, most online games will deal you some virtual chips. So online table games still respect the gaming principle of offline table games; they just enrich it with a few additional features, that’s all!\r\n\r\nBasically, if you know how to play poker or blackjack at a classic casino, you won’t need any kind of  tutorial for the online version of these games. The only thing you need to bear in mind when it comes to online casinos and chips is that references to “chips” sometimes stand