n) psychological effect tied to playing with tokens. It’s somehow easier for people to be reckless with chips than with real bills.\r\n\r\nSo now we’ve learned the “why,” now let’s examine the “where.” Which casino games have chips on the table? Let’s see!\r\n<h2>The Practice — Which Games Use Chips?</h2>\r\nCasinos offer tokens for playing various games. At some casinos, each game has its own tokens. At others, multiple games are played with the same type of tokens. However, in the majority of casinos, tokens for slots differ from tokens for any other games. Tokens for slots are usually made of metal, and they resemble coins. Now, classic casino clay-based chips, a token which we are talking about in the article, are usually used in four casino games.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Blackjack — Chips are used for blackjack in almost all casinos.</li>\r\n 	<li>Roulette — It’s quite well-known that roulette wagers are made with chips, both in the European and American variants of roulette.</li>\r\n 	<li>Poker — We guess you already knew that chips are always used for poker wagering.</li>\r\n 	<li>Craps — In the popular casino game of craps, chips are used for betting too.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nSince we now know which games use casino tokens, let’s find out what various tokens mean. As you already know, these tokens come in many different colors. Each color symbolizes a different value, so it’s quite important to know what each color means. So let’s learn about the colors now!\r\n<h2>The Colorful World of Chips — The Meaning Behind the Colors</h2>\r\nThe relation between a chip color and value can sometimes vary from casino to casino. However, there are some common, universally accepted rules that you come across in most casinos around the world. Sometimes, there are rules about colors and values of chips on the state level. All in all, some globally known standards usually apply in all gambling establishments; at least in most of them, anyway!\r\n\r\nFor instance, many people, even thos