ou can guess from the title of this section, collecting chips is called exonumia. The price of these collectible items ranges from as low as $5 to as high as $500. The price of an antique casino token depends on the date of manufacture, the state it’s in, its relative rarity, or some special features; just as you would expect with other antiquities in general. And since we’ve just acquainted ourselves with antique chips, let’s meet one more special type of token — the nonmaterial ones!\r\n<h2>Virtual Gambling — Chips in Online Casinos</h2>\r\nIn brick-and-mortar casinos, chips stand for real money. In online casinos, real money stands for chips. Wait, what? Confused...? We’ll explain now!\r\n\r\nOnline casinos often use the term “free chips,” which stands for a real-money bonus. You can get free chips at an online casino; even for games that don’t feature chips per se, such as slots. However, online casinos, chips don’t always stand for bonuses and promotions; they often represent real chips at virtual table games. This way, when you play online poker or online blackjack, most online games will deal you some virtual chips. So online table games still respect the gaming principle of offline table games; they just enrich it with a few additional features, that’s all!\r\n\r\nBasically, if you know how to play poker or blackjack at a classic casino, you won’t need any kind of  tutorial for the online version of these games. The only thing you need to bear in mind when it comes to online casinos and chips is that references to “chips” sometimes stand for a specific amount of real money. And with this thought, we conclude our chips tutorial. But have a little read of our summary before we say goodbye!\r\n<h2>Final Word</h2>\r\nChips come in all colors and weights — it depends on the manufacturer, purpose, or casino preferences. It’s quite easy to grasp the relation between colors and value; just follow our tables. It is legal to take chips from a casino, as long as you don’t try to sell them. You can, however, sell expired ones to collectors. Also, you can tip casino employees with chips; that practice is not against any regulations. Actually, it’s even preferable for you to tip casino personnel, either with real money or chips — this is an important part of casino etiquette. By the way, online casinos sometimes call amounts of real money chips, even with games that don’t even feature chips at all.\r\n\r\nThere is usually a logical correlation between the chip with the smallest value and the minimum bet. Also, there is often a correlation between the chip with the highest value and the maximum-size bet. So before you sit down at the casino table, ask about the lowest and the highest buy-in, as well as the lowest and the highest wagers you are permitted. So when you enquire about the wagering policy for a certain table in advance, you can easily make your decision about what chips you are going to use the most. We hope that whichever chips you choose, they are going to bring you luck!', 'Chips in Casino — The Full Guide', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '232-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-12-05 18:52:00', '2019-12-05 16:52:00', '', 232, 'http://aussieplay-blog.local/bez-kategorii/232-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
