ic amount of real money. And with this thought, we conclude our chips tutorial. But have a little read of our summary before we say goodbye!\r\n<h2>Final Word</h2>\r\nChips come in all colors and weights — it depends on the manufacturer, purpose, or casino preferences. It’s quite easy to grasp the relation between colors and value; just follow our tables. It is legal to take chips from a casino, as long as you don’t try to sell them. You can, however, sell expired ones to collectors. Also, you can tip casino employees with chips; that practice is not against any regulations. Actually, it’s even preferable for you to tip casino personnel, either with real money or chips — this is an important part of casino etiquette. By the way, online casinos sometimes call amounts of real money chips, even with games that don’t even feature chips at all.\r\n\r\nThere is usually a logical correlation between the chip with the smallest value and the minimum bet. Also, there is often a correlation between the chip with the highest value and the maximum-size bet. So before you sit down at the casino table, ask about the lowest and the highest buy-in, as well as the lowest and the highest wagers you are permitted. So when you enquire about the wagering policy for a certain table in advance, you can easily make your decision about what chips you are going to use the most. We hope that whichever chips you choose, they are going to bring you luck!', 'Chips in Casino — The Full Guide', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '232-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-12-06 15:30:46', '2019-12-06 13:30:46', '', 232, 'http://aussieplay-blog.local/bez-kategorii/232-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(292, 1, '2019-12-06 20:02:16', '2019-12-06 18:02:16', 'Whether you call it a puggy (Scotland), fruit machine (England), pokie (Australia), one-armed bandit (in American slang), or simply slot, it’s hard to deny how fun and exciting this popular game is. And there’s no place on the planet, no matter how isolated, where you won’t find it. And whatever they call it there, there’s probably a long queue to play it too!\r\n\r\nWith the internet, slots literally entered our homes. And not only that: by now, you can also enjoy them on your mobile phones and tablets. So it’s safe to say that slots are everywhere. Some gamers like the shiny glamour of a casino, while others prefer to play at home with no distractions; but everybody loves the one-armed bandit!\r\n<h2>Behind the Mask</h2>\r\nSlots have a specific appeal because they represent a true gamble. One simple spin, and you can become a millionaire! Or stay empty-handed and pissed. But whatever the case, you probably won’t end up waiting too long before you enjoy another round. Yes, the slots are highly addictive, and you should be wary; but that’s a whole other topic, and we’ll get to it later! So, let’s peek behind the glitzy mask first, and see how they work.\r\n<h2>How Slots Work</h2>\r\nThe classic slot layout is a display with three or more reels with various symbols on them. The reels rotate when you pull a lever or push the button. After a spin, the reels come to a stop and show a combination of symbols as a result. Depending on this combo, you have either won, or you’ve lost! Seems pretty simple, and it is. Maybe slots owe their popularity to their simplicity? Because unlike many other casino games, they don’t require any special skill set at all!\r\n<h3>Paytable</h3>\r\nTo figure out if you’ve actually won something, you should consult the paytable. This shows you if your combo is a winning one; and if so, what you win. It is usually situated above (or maybe below) the reels. Video versions have a “Paytable” button that opens a screen with all the info.\r\n\r\nYou would usually need two or more symbols to qualify for any type of win. The wins do not automatically mean you’ve won some money, though. Sometimes, they might be free spins and other bonus features that you can benefit from. There is a lot of other useful info in the table, so you should always consult it.\r\n\r\nIf we take a look at one of the games, the picture may become clearer. Naughty or Nice from RealTime Gaming is a popular slot, with a naughty twist on the Christmas theme. If we check the paytable we can see that the lowest-paying symbol is 200 coins, while the highest-paying is Santa himself, awarding you a staggering 2,500 coins. This piece of info is useful, because it immediately says that this is a high-volatility slot. We will explain the volatility later, but bear in mind that this can help you determine if it’s the game for you.\r\n\r\nAs we said, sometimes you don’t really win money, but free spins and other bonuses. In every game there is a scatter card which usually triggers the special features. Also, each slot will have a wild symbol that replaces any other to make the winning combo. You don’t literally have to have five Santas to hit the prize in Naughty or Nice Slot. There can be four of them plus the Naughty symbol (wild card) and you are a winner.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-303\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/giphy-1.gif\" alt=\"Slot Gif \" width=\"480\" height=\"270\" />\r\n\r\nYou should regard the pay tables as slot maps, and always go through them. Nobody likes to get lost in unknown territory. Especially if you wagered some money!\r\n<h3>Jackpots</h3>\r\nWe’re all chasing the big prize, and a jackpot is essentially what we hope for when we play. It is the best prize you can possibly hope for when playing slots. Jackpots can be fixed or progressive; this means either that the prize is always the same, or that it rises as the game goes on. A progressive jackpot increases as the game progresses, but only if nobody wins the main prize.\r\n\r\nWhen somebody finally does hit it, the jackpot resets itself back to the initial amount. The normal jackpot will stay exactly the same, regardless of how many bets have been placed.\r\n\r\nThere is also a pooled jackpot, which is the biggest possible win in the slot business.This means players from various sites all contribute to the same prize, so the amounts can really go sky-high! RealTime Gaming offers this alluring prize on their Shopping Spree slot and the highest payout was a mind-blowing $1.25 million in 2011. The current jackpot on this very game is now $2 million, so we’re on the verge of breaking that record soon.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-298\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ezgif-6-bb9436d6e281.gif\" alt=\"Slot Gif \" width=\"499\" height=\"257\" />\r\n\r\nHowever, the same games can be produced with different characteristics, so once again you should read your pay tables. The jackpot details will be there. When it comes to playing the slots, take nothing for granted.\r\n<h3>Sound Like a Pro</h3>\r\nThere is a specific terminology connected to slots, and it’s beneficial to learn it. You wouldn’t want to get baffled mid-game! And it’s much cooler to sound like an experienced player, isn’t it?\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A wild card is a symbol that can usually substitute for others and help you make the winning combination. Sometimes, it can act as a multiplier, meaning that it doubles or triples the wins.</li>\r\n 	<li>A scatter most often serves to open a bonus play and free spins. You would need three or more in order to do so. In most games, wilds cannot replace scatters.</li>\r\n 	<li>Bonus is a free game that you can play if you land a certain combination. It can be either a certain number of free spins or another special feature. The wins in the course of bonus rounds might be even higher than during normal play.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBut to be a pro, one has to know about the history of the game. It may also broaden our perspective on how one-armed bandits work.\r\n<h2>The Origins of Slots</h2>\r\nThis distant relative of the modern slot is the gambling machine that Sittman and Pitt from Brooklyn invented in 1891. They based the game on poker. The machine had five drums and 50 cards. The gamblers had to insert a coin and pull the lever. Then, the drums would spin and give out a result. In order to pay out, it would have to be a successful poker hand.\r\n\r\nThe local venue would determine what the wins are, and usually, they would give out free drinks or food. They would usually remove two cards from the deck to reduce the chances of winning.\r\n<h2>Protoslot</h2>\r\nThe payouts proved to be complicated due to a significant number of possible combinations. But the popularity of the game inspired Charles Fay to design a much simpler, yet even more popular machine.\r\n\r\nSomewhere between 1887 and 1895, he came up with a mechanism of three reels and five symbols. The number of combos was much lower, so the instant payout system was devised. The highest-paying symbol was a bell, and three in a row would award the first-ever jackpot.\r\n\r\nLiberty Bell was a smashing success and became the central point of any respectable saloon in California. Even when some states banned gaming devices, Fay could not produce enough of them to satisfy market demand.\r\n\r\nThe slots developed almost exponentially to the demand for them. In 1963, Bally presented the first electromechanical slot, and it was the famous Money Honey. This beauty could give 500 coins payout without the attendant’s assistance. It changed the industry forever!\r\n<h2>The Rise of Slots</h2>\r\nThe contemporary gaming industry has many branches and offers various games for all tastes. However, since the mid 20th century, the biggest part of the business has been the slots. Regardless of the continent, slots make more than 70% of casino incomes.\r\n\r\nWhile you’re walking the casino floors in Monte Carlo, Macau, or Vegas, you can see that it’s the aisles of slots that take up the most space. And the ecstatic sound of coins bursting out of the machine when a player hits the jackpot is like nothing else you can experience in the world of gambling!\r\n\r\nSlots are the biggest money-makers in the industry; and indeed, the favourites of every casino owner. So why do we fall for them when we can only guess how favourable they are to our opponents? Because they are soooo fun!\r\n\r\nModern slots are, however, a far cry from Liberty Bell. They are way more intricate in design, backdrops, and payouts. But the pivotal thing to know is that they are computers with an infinite number of possibilities, as well as close-to-zero chances of malfunction. The lever on the side and retro details are a mere legacy; because video really did kill the mechanical star!\r\n<h2>Video</h2>\r\nWhen microprocessors appeared, the game changed and took a turn that Fay could have hardly expected when he made Liberty Bell. Now, inside every machine, there is a computer that replaced the old mechanism.\r\n\r\nFortune Coin Company presented the first real video slot in 1976. It grabbed the attention of casino owners immediately, and Las Vegas Hilton was the first venue to offer it to their clients; as soon as the Nevada State Gaming Commission approved.\r\n\r\nVideo slots made a range of possibilities available. They became interactive, as well as much more advanced in terms of graphic design and other effects. More importantly, the video option opened the door to more complex features in terms of payouts, bonuses, and gameplay.\r\n\r\nFirst of all, the standard three-reel machine gave way to a five-reel version, with 50 symbols on a reel. The odds, as you can guess, became much higher. The game providers can offer much higher prizes now and still keep the edge. With many options to choose from and many ways to win, slots benefited immensely from computerization. As did the providers!\r\n\r\nAny slot you play now is a computerized machine. They became standard in classic and online casinos since the 1980s. And that’s a useful piece of info for any player who is just getting to know the one-armed bandit. Whether you are tapping the screen of your smartphone or pulling a lever on a casino floor, the principle stays the same.\r\n<h2>Let’s Talk Numbers</h2>\r\nOh, don’t run away! It’s just a bit of math, but it can really help you. You should always bear in mind that slots are a game of chance. Coming up with patterns and tactics to beat them is futile and can only make you waste your time.\r\n\r\nTo understand why, we just have to look at the way slots function. The old machines had three reels with ten symbols on a reel, thus giving out 1,000 combos. A pretty simple equation: 10³ = 1,000. The issue was that it wasn’t suitable for awarding high wins, due to the limited number of combinations. The number of symbols rose to 22, allowing 10,648 combos; but the prize still had to remain pretty limited in size!\r\n\r\nIn 1984, a Random Number Generator (RNG) entered the stage, and things have never been the same again… This is a special kind of software that picks out a random combination of numbers, making hundreds of thousands of combinations per second. Every numerical combo is assigned to a specific symbol you see on the reels, which provides an opportunity for many different variations.\r\n\r\nA virtual reel of the slot that has (say) 256 virtual stops can give 16,777,216 positions. This allowed casinos to offer huge prizes on small bets, because they are sure they can happen every 16.7 million times. This is a long-term calculation and can only secure casinos over a longer period of time; because you can also hit the prize on the very first spin!\r\n<h2>Players vs. RNG</h2>\r\nThere are two characteristics of RNG that you need to fathom:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>It runs non-stop. It doesn’t matter if the slot is dormant or active, RNG is always working, choosing numbers and picking those combinations.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-300\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Hnet.com-image-1.gif\" alt=\"Slot Gif \" width=\"380\" height=\"214\" />\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li>In the case of RNG, every new pick is programmed as an independent event. This means that previous combinations do not influence the new ones.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIn actual play, every time we spin, we play a new game, and none of the results we had before has anything to do with the one we are expecting. The keyword to remember here is “random.” Because the slots are, of course, random by nature!\r\n\r\nWith every round, we have a possibility of hitting the jackpot. However, if it hasn’t been won for a long time, it doesn’t mean that our chances are improving. If a certain machine gives out the prize on average once every 10,000 spins, it can give three jackpots in a row. But it can also skip it for 20,000 or even 50,000 spins. Sound cruel? Maybe, but it’s also a pretty fair way of doing it!\r\n\r\nAfter all, randomness means that all players stand on an equal footing, because we all have exactly the same chance of winning. So when you fully grasp this concept, you can finally be immune to the various myths surrounding this game. Seductive, but mostly untrue, such rumours have lead many players astray in their pursuit of some cunning strategies to help them beat the machines.\r\n<h2>How to Beat Slots</h2>\r\nIn short, you can’t! Slots are a game of chance, and no secret strategy or plan will help you beat them. Legends of loose machines and certain times of a day or year that you should play at are sheer fiction. But let’s go through them and see what they’re all about.\r\n<h3>Loose Machine</h3>\r\nTales of “loose machine” are very old, and date back to the time of mechanical slots. The idea is that such machines give out prizes more often, due to a mechanical malfunction; and that the prizes are enormous! However, there is no evidence that such a machine exists, and if it does, the tiniest sign of malfunction would lead the owners to remove it from the casino floor.\r\n\r\nAnd with computerized slots, this is even more unlikely! The state-of-the-art software built in the modern games would notice any kind of corruption, and alert the providers to either fix it or make the slot unavailable.\r\n<h3>Winning Time</h3>\r\nAnother common myth is that casinos tighten slots on weekends and holidays, to make sure not too many jackpots get hit. However, the time and bureaucracy required to change a specific slot feature are substantial. Legal casinos would not do this. Also, by checking the paytable, you can get some important info, and see for yourself if they’re any different from the last time you played!\r\n\r\nSo instead of focusing on beating the computer, maybe we should concentrate on the kinds of things that really can help us improve our chances.\r\n<h2>Strategies</h2>\r\nThe wisest strategy for any game is to come prepared and informed. The best tactics are to fight the battles that you can, and make the most out of your situation. So let’s apply this approach to the slots and devise a couple of tips that can come in handy.\r\n<h3>Scouting</h3>\r\nBefore you play for actual money, try many of the free play options that casinos offer. We already said that slots are run by computers now, and every machine is different than the other. To understand how jackpot work, but also multipliers, wilds, scatters, and bonuses, find a slot you like and explore the demo mode. This will make it familiar, and you won’t come across any unpleasant surprises when you start betting.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-301\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/3783.jpg\" alt=\"Guy playing slots\" width=\"480\" height=\"269\" />\r\n<h3>Thrifting</h3>\r\