ing, each making 1,000 spins. This amounts to 100,000 spins. Dividing this by 10,000, we can expect 10 jackpots to be won in total!\r\n\r\nNow, let’s imagine it’s Saturday and that 1,000 people are playing 1,000 spins per person. That’s a million spins, providing an estimated 100 jackpots! Sounds better? Well actually, it’s exactly the same. 10x more prizes for 10x more players.\r\n\r\n[supsystic-tables id=11]\r\n\r\nAs you can see, your odds are the same; so you can choose whichever day of the week is most convenient for you.\r\n<h3>Bankroll Guru</h3>\r\nThere are a lot of things we cannot control when we play slots. However, there’s one thing we do have a lot of control over, and that’s our bankroll. Of all the strategies you’re going to hear about, money management is the cornerstone. So here are some tips on how to do it.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><img class=\"size-full wp-image-423 alignright\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/hg.jpg\" alt=\"Coins in Casino \" width=\"225\" height=\"263\" />Set a budget and stick to it! Don’t go on a wild goose chase, just because you have a gut feeling. Controlling your bankroll is really important and can help you stay in the game. It can even take you to that grand prize if you’re careful!</li>\r\n 	<li>We all want to win big, but sometimes you have to invest a little more to hit the jackpot. Come up with a plan based on whatever information you can get about the volatility of the slot.</li>\r\n 	<li>Don’t spend your resources if you don’t have to! Always try the slot in demo mode first, to figure out how the jackpot and multipliers work. This can assist you with creating some bankroll tactics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Very Best Time</h2>\r\nIt looks like there is no particular date or time of the year we can choose to effectively increase our odds of winning that coveted jackpot. However, there is still the best time for you. Play when you have the money, play when you’re feeling up to the game, and play