r local Sidney venue, pokie machines will occupy the biggest portion of the casino.\r\n\r\nPokies are a true gamble, and that’s a huge part of their appeal. The rush of winning, the gratification of instant success, and euphoric sound of the coins bursting out of the machine have been successfully luring gamers into gambling venues for over a century. It’s a favorite game among casino owners, while it’s also the biggest moneymaker in the industry. Pokies amount to 75% of the total income for casinos in Australia, and the figure is more or less the same anywhere in the world!\r\n\r\nThe internet successfully propelled pokies into worldwide superstardom, making this guilty pleasure available for everyone. And with the various exciting online versions out there, the stories on how to win grew even wilder, so that elusive jackpot seemed to inch closer and closer over time. The pokies aka slots were invented by Charles Fay in America, somewhere between 1887 and 1895. The name of the game was Liberty Bell, and Fay was inspired by the poker machines. He simplified the principle by reducing the number of reels to three, which in turn granted an effective payout system.\r\n\r\nPokies became an instant success and quickly spread across the continents. They arrived in Australia in the early 20th century and only grew in fame and notoriety.\r\n<h2>Inside Out</h2>\r\nBut how do they work? Well, the gameplay is straightforward and doesn’t require any particular skill set.\r\n<h3>Out</h3>\r\nHere’s the step-by-step guide if you play in a classic casino:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Insert a coin into the machine</li>\r\n 	<li>Place the bet</li>\r\n 	<li>Spin the reels</li>\r\n 	<li>Wait for the results</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOnce the results are displayed, you will automatically know whether you won or not. And if you choose to play at the online casino, everything is even easier.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-524\" src=\"http://aussieplay-blog.local/wp-content/uploads/201