play and knowing how to win are two entirely different things. So while you’re doing next to nothing, the machine inside is playing a way more intricate game.\r\n<h3>Inside</h3>\r\nThe first pokies were simple machines. They had three reels with each reel containing ten symbols. This set-up amounted to a thousand combinations. If three identical symbols appeared on one line, you would win the prize. But because of the limited number of combos, the jackpots had to stay limited as well. The casinos could not offer million-dollar rewards for one-dollar bets.\r\n\r\nIn the 1980s, everything began to change with the computerization of pokie machines. Although the number of symbols rose to 22 and made 10,648 winning combinations possible, it wasn’t until 1984 that the random number generator was introduced and the jackpots started to get truly massive.\r\n<h2>RNG Reign</h2>\r\nWith the digital era, the developers are not restricted to a certain number of reels and symbols. The possibilities are becoming endless. If, for example, a virtual reel has 256 stops per line, it amounts to 256³ possibilities. That means there are 16,777,216 outcomes in total.\r\n\r\nThe game providers were able to offer enormous jackpots because the prizes would occur every 16.7 million plays. This is a long-term prediction, however; because due to RNG you can also win on the first spin!\r\n\r\nThe random number generators brought true randomness to pokies. It is highly sophisticated software, which is designed to make every outcome in the game perfectly random. Two pieces of info are vital when we discuss RNG.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>They never stop working. It doesn’t matter if you or someone else is not playing the pokie. The RNG picks those random numbers non-stop.</li>\r\n 	<li>As a result of this, every spin is an independent event and is not at all connected to the previous outcome.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA concept of randomness is not easy to grasp, especially when you put all your lucky charms and intuition into play; but it’s most definitely there! The good thing about it is that the games are not tampered with in any way, and because of this, all the players are on an equal footing.\r\n<h2>Casino Rules</h2>\r\nWhen you enter a casino, be it a real one or a virtual one, the odds are not in your favour. You’ve probably heard a lot about the house edge; and if you’re not sure how it works, we’ll try to explain it for you now.\r\n\r\nTo understand the edge, you should look into the RTP or the Return to Player percentage. This number is usually available for any machine that you play. It is the percentage that the casino pays out on your wins. So they never pay out 100% of the total wagered money; but rather, somewhere between 91–97% (in the case of pokies).\r\n\r\nThe casino keeps the remaining amount and thus they manage to earn some money. Let’s break it down into a simple table:\r\n\r\n[supsystic-tables id=13]\r\n\r\nSo when you lose, you lose it all. But when you win, you don’t really win it all! And although it sounds unfair, there is still a possibility for you to win the jackpot in your first round. RTP rules make the casinos profitable in the long-term; however, short-term outcomes cannot be predicted with any accuracy.\r\n<h2>How to Beat that Pokie?</h2>\r\nYou’ve probably realized up by now that these machines make for some pretty fierce adversaries. So instead of trying to come up with solutions to beat them, let’s try to find ways to improve our odds.\r\n<h3>Prep, Prep, Prep</h3>\r\nExplore the battleground! In order to promote their business, casinos offer many options for free play or demo mode. You can learn a lot about pokies before you wager your money. Find out everything you can about the wilds, scatters, multipliers, and bonus features of the particular machine. This will give you an idea about what kind of bankroll strategy you should apply.\r\n<h3>Beat the Casino</h3>\r\nAs we have said, in this competitive industry, game providers are not thrifty when it comes to marketing. They offer a lot of free stuff to attract players! Become a member of a casino club, and subscribe to the newsletters. This is where you can find a lot of bonuses and special offers. You can even win without investing in real cash. If you don’t, you get to play and learn with your bankroll intact.\r\n<h3>Stay Grounded</h3>\r\nDon’t go chasing myths about loose machines and elaborate tactics! All these tales about corrupt machines that give out enormous prizes seem even less plausible when you consider the state-of-the-art software they’ve incorporated into the pokie machines. You’re playing against the computer. The levers on the side and retro details are just for show, inspired by the legacy of old-school manual pokie machines. Instead, you can direct your strategy and funds towards succeeding in the battles you actually have a hope of winning!\r\n\r\nThe same goes for your bankroll. Don’t be careless, but be aware that most machines are going to give away those jackpots for minimum bets. Try to allocate the funds properly, so you can stay in the game but also get the chance to win the big prize.\r\n<h3>Wise Choices</h3>\r\nAlways check the RTP. It will show you a number of things about the pokies. Don’t squander your resources, and only play games with RTP of 96% and higher. Manage your bankroll with care, so that you can play longer. According to many gamers, you should avoid the most obvious pokies. The ones that are heavily advertised are precisely the ones that the casinos would like you to play, and that’s not good! Same goes for branded pokies. Their primary purpose is to attract inexperienced players and take their money.\r\n\r\nAlso, make sure you understand the volatility of the machine before you start betting. Low-volatility means that the pokie awards lower sums but more frequently, and high-volatility implies that the prizes are rare but generous. This is an important factor to consider, and it can help you get better at the game.\r\n<h2>In a Nutshell</h2>\r\nNo, we cannot beat the pokies. But, then again, they cannot beat us either! The best way to win is to play and play wisely. Randomness does not favour anyone, so the game is fair. And a lot of fun, to boot! What more could you possibly ask for?', 'How to Win at Pokies', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '513-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-12-16 14:52:54', '2019-12-16 12:52:54', '', 513, 'http://aussieplay-blog.local/bez-kategorii/513-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
